  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening of social organizations in risk management and climate change in Lomas de Carabayllo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on the experience and success of a previous project with Misereor, CIDAP will implement a three-year project working with 12 different communities in Lomas de Carabayllo, Lima, focusing on climate change adaptation, reducing risk to disasters, youth environmental leadership and the conservation of Lomas de la Primavera. To this end, CIDAP will implement a comprehensive capacity development programme encompassing practical courses on risk management, Community Risk Management Plans and Community Response Plans. Based on these plans, CIDAP will provide technical assistance to implement practical actions on disaster risk reduction and adaptation to climate change. CIDAP will also implement a programme to strengthen the capacity of 27 leaders from social organisations (including youth groups) to conserve Loma de Primavera. Advocacy and campaign strategies will be developed calling for the recognition of Lomas de Primavera as a Natural Protected Area along with activities seeking to promote it as an eco-tourism and research destination for schools and universities.</narrative>
  </description>
